parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause the vehicle to stall, overheat, or leak coolant, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates
coolant leaks
steam comes from under the hood
the engine overheats
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may experience rough idling or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant leaks can cause the engine to overheat, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
steam comes from under the hood
and the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or rubbery
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle wanders or drifts on the road
the steering column moves or rattles
the vehicle makes a loud slamming or clunking noise when going over bumps or dips.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tie rod falls off or breaks while driving
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle makes a loud noise when going over bumps or dips.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The key will not turn in the ignition
the steering wheel locks up
the key is difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The bolt that holds the ball joint in place becomes loose
causing the ball joint to fail
leading to a sudden loss of control while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear end of the vehicle skidding can cause loss of control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear end of the vehicle skids or jumps sideways when hitting a hole
bump
or uneven road
especially at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor front end alignment can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
especially on wet pavement
and the front end alignment is poor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Suspension failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a hard ride
making it difficult to control steering
and the suspension design is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unstable vehicle handling can cause loss of control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a sudden jerk or pull to one side while driving
especially on wet pavement or when hitting a hole or bump.
